.:: Einstein-puzzle ::.

5 different games are played: billiard, bridge, chess, backgammon, go
There are 5 different nationalities: british, danish, german, norwegian, swede
There are 5 different favourite beverages: beer, coffee, milk, tea, water
5 different brands of cigars are smoked: billiardmaster, dunhill, pall-mall, prince, blend
City: hamburg, colone, hannover, nizza, london
1. the british is the person playing chess
2. the swedish is the person traveling to hannover
3. the danish is the person drinking tea
4. the person playing bridge is on the left of the person playing backgammon
5. the person playing bridge is the person drinking coffee
6. the pall-mall-smoker is the person traveling to colone
7. the person playing go is the dunhill-smoker
8. the person drinking milk is in the middle
9. the norwegian is on the far left
10. the blend-smoker is on the left or right of the person traveling to hamburg
11. the person traveling to londons is on the left or right of the dunhill-smoker
12. the billiardmaster-smoker is the person drinking beer
13. the german is the prince-smoker
14. the norwegian is on the left or right of the person playing billiard
15. the blend-smoker is on the left or right of the person drinking water

.:: Answer ::.
|		|	1	|	2	|	3	|	4	|	5	|
| Game		|    go	|     billiard	|      chess	|     bridge	|     backgammon	|
| Nationality	|   norwegian	|    danish	|    british	|    german	|    swedish	|
| City		|     hamburg	|    london	|     colone	|     nizza	|      hannover	|
| Beverage	|    water	|     tea	|     milk	|    coffee	|      beer	|
| Cigar		|   dunhill	|    blend	|  pall-mall	|    prince	|   billiardmaster	|
